---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="About | XXIV ARCHIVE">

<section class="hero">

    <p>THE visit</p>

    <h1>
        More than music.<br>
        A living git add museum.
    </h1>

</section>

<section class="story">

<div class="container">

<h2>Our Philosophy</h2>

<p>

XXIV ARCHIVE exists to preserve moments rather than simply release music.

Every song becomes an exhibition.

Every exhibition is accompanied by photography, written reflections and visual documentation.

Rather than disappearing into a catalogue of releases, every project remains part of a growing permanent collection.

The archive grows with every chapter.

</p>

</div>

</section>

<section class="artist">

<div class="container">

<h2>The Artist</h2>

<p>

I don't see music as isolated songs.

Every project represents a period of my life.

The sounds, photographs and publications preserve those moments exactly as they were experienced.

XXIV ARCHIVE is where those moments remain accessible long after the music is released.

</p>

</div>

</section>

</BaseLayout>

